<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="4421">
This species can be recognized by the lanceolate or elliptical-lanceolate leaves, with inconspicuous or slightly prominulous veins (
<bibRefCitation author="Leon, B." journalOrPublisher="Aarhus Universitet, Aarhus" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" title="A taxonomic revision of the fern genus Campyloneurum (Polypodiaceae)" year="1993">
<normalizedToken originalValue="León">Leon</normalizedToken>
1993
</bibRefCitation>
). The closest species is 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Polypodiaceae" genus="Campyloneurum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Campyloneurum xalapense" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xalapense">Campyloneurum xalapense</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Fée">Fee</normalizedToken>
, from which it differs by the leave shape (
<bibRefCitation author="Leon, B." journalOrPublisher="Aarhus Universitet, Aarhus" pageId="0" pageNumber="4421" title="A taxonomic revision of the fern genus Campyloneurum (Polypodiaceae)" year="1993">
<normalizedToken originalValue="León">Leon</normalizedToken>
1993
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
